Rating: 4
This was my first attempt at pastry cream. Used it as a filling for boston cream pie. I took the other reviewers' advice and used 3T of corn starch. Also the first time I've cooked with a dry vanilla bean. The cream turned out beautifully, was delicious and the recipe yielded more than enough to do the trick. I know I will come back to this recipe again and again.

Rating: 0
The most delicious pastry cream I have ever tasted. It tastes like pastry cream you would purchase at the best bakeries in NYC. I have used this pastry cream as a filler in rum cake and it is quite a big hit!

